<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SkillsCraft</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
       body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        pre {
            background-color: #2d2d2d;
            color: #f8f8f2;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-x: auto;
            max-width: 800px;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-wrap: break-word;
        }
         .keyword { color: #66d9ef; }
        .function { color: #a6e22e; }
        .string { color: #e6db74; }
        .comment { color: #75715e; }
        .number { color: #ae81ff; }

        
        </style>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-100">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    {{>navbar}}

    <div class="flex">

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        {{>js_sidebar}}

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="ml-0 md:ml-64 w-full">
            <div class="container mx-auto p-6">

                <!-- Section: Core Concepts of HTML -->
                <section class="mb-12">
                    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Syntax</h1>

                    <!-- Concept 1: Introduction to HTML -->
                    <div class="mb-8">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">JavaScript Syntax</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            JavaScript syntax is the set of rules, how JavaScript programs are constructed:
                           </p>
                        <div id="code-block">
        <pre>
<span class="comment">// How to create variables:</span>
<span class="keyword">var x;</span>
<span class="keyword">let y;</span>

<span class="comment">// How to use variables:</span>
<span class="keyword">x = <span class="number">5</span>; </span>
<span class="keyword">y = <span class="number">6</span>; </span>
<span class="keyword">let z = x + y; </span>
  </pre>
    </div>
    <br>
     <button id="copy-button" class="absolute bg-blue-600 text-white py-1 px-3 rounded hover:bg-blue-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring focus:ring-blue-300">
                Copy
            </button>

                    </div>
<br>
                    <!-- Concept 2: Basic HTML Structure -->
                   <div class="mb-8">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">JavaScript Values</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                    <strong>        The JavaScript syntax defines two types of values:</strong>
                    <hr>
Fixed values
<br>
<br>
Variable values
<br>
<br>
Fixed values are called Literals.
